<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="424" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1616,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1796,1822]" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">Comments.</emphasis>
The generic placement is tentative and because of the similarity of RTA, elongate tegular apophysis (
<emphasis box="[161,188,1833,1858]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">Ta</emphasis>
), long embolus, and round receptacles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="424" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1616,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1868,1894]" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Both sexes differ from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ovtchinnikov" authorityYear="2006" box="[597,757,1868,1894]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Indozodion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inayatullahi">
<emphasis box="[597,757,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">I. inayatullahi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the dark anterior part of carapace (
<emphasis box="[1202,1225,1869,1894]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">vs</emphasis>
. almost uniformly colored). The male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Roewer" authorityYear="1960" box="[405,532,1904,1930]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Zodarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lindbergi">
<emphasis box="[405,532,1904,1930]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">I. lindbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from that of the generotype by the absence of strong setae on the palpal tibia and RTA (
<emphasis box="[325,348,1941,1966]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">vs</emphasis>
. present), and the slightly bent tip of RTA directed anteriorly (
<emphasis box="[1060,1083,1941,1966]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">vs</emphasis>
. bent at about 45º and directed dorsally). The epigyne of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Roewer" authorityYear="1960" box="[444,570,1976,2002]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Zodarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lindbergi">
<emphasis box="[444,570,1976,2002]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">I. lindbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks anterior transversal pits (
<emphasis box="[924,947,1977,2002]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">vs</emphasis>
. present in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ovtchinnikov" authorityYear="2006" box="[1080,1239,1976,2003]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Indozodion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inayatullahi">
<emphasis box="[1080,1089,1977,2002]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">I</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1104,1239,1976,2002]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">inayatullahi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and receptacles are more widely separated (by 4.5 diameters 
<emphasis box="[655,678,2013,2038]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">vs</emphasis>
. less than 
<quantity box="[797,840,2012,2038]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="1" pageNumber="424" unit="in" value="3.0">3 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ovtchinnikov" authorityYear="2006" box="[846,1005,2012,2039]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Indozodion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inayatullahi">
<emphasis box="[846,855,2013,2038]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">I</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[870,1005,2012,2038]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="424">inayatullahi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="427" pageId="2" pageNumber="425" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,150,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="425">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,150,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="425">Description.</emphasis>
Male (specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[610,710,151,178]" name="Pakistan" pageId="2" pageNumber="425">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
). Habitus as in 
<figureCitation box="[891,982,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1688,1712]" captionTargetBox="[154,1420,388,1665]" captionTargetId="figure-125@2.[151,1436,381,1665]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Habitus and male palp of Indozodion lindbergi (Roewer, 1960). A male habitus, dorsal; B female habitus, dorsal; C–F palp, dorsal, retrolateral, prolateral and ventral. Scale bars = 0.2 mm, unless stated otherwise. Abbreviations: Ta—tegular apophysis, Tl—lamellar extension of the tegular apophysis, Va—ventro-retrolateral apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683466" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683466/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="425">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
. Total length 3.45. Carapace 1.65 long, 1.23 wide. Eye sizes: AME: 0.13, ALE: 0.11, PME: 0.08, PLE: 0.09. Carapace, sternum, labium, chelicerae and maxillae yellowish; carapace with irregular dark patterns on pars cephalica. Legs yellowish, without annulations. Abdomen dorsally grayish and with scattered darker patches; grayish brown ventrally. Spinnerets pale, uniform in color. Measurements of legs: I: 5.67 (1.57, 0.54, 1.38, 1.27, 0.91), II: 5.66 (1.52, 0.56, 1.19, 1.44, 0.95), III: 5.50 (1.50, 0.59, 1.08, 1.51, 0.82), Fe IV: 2.00, rest of the segments missing.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683466" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6683466" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683466/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="425" startId="2.[151,250,1688,1712]" targetBox="[154,1420,388,1665]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1688,1784]" pageId="2" pageNumber="425">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,1688,1712]" pageId="2" pageNumber="425">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
Habitus and male palp of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Roewer, 1960)" authorityName="Zamani &amp; Marusik" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Roewer" baseAuthorityYear="1960" box="[547,929,1688,1712]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Indozodion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="425" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lindbergi">
<emphasis box="[547,760,1688,1712]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="425">Indozodion lindbergi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Roewer, C. F." box="[774,921,1688,1712]" pageId="2" pageNumber="425" pagination="1 - 53" refId="ref6705" refString="Roewer, C. F. (1960) Solifugen und Opilioniden - Araneae Orthognathae, Haplogynae und Entelegynae (Contribution a l'etude de la faune d'Afghanistan 23). Goteborgs Kungliga Vetenskaps och Vitterhets Samhalles Handlingar, Series 6, B 8 (7), 1 - 53." type="journal article" year="1960">Roewer, 1960</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. A male habitus, dorsal; B female habitus, dorsal; C–F palp, dorsal, retrolateral, prolateral and ventral. Scale bars = 0.2 mm, unless stated otherwise. Abbreviations: 
<emphasis box="[1319,1366,1725,1748]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="425">Ta—</emphasis>
tegular apophysis, 
<emphasis box="[265,309,1760,1784]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="425">Tl—</emphasis>
lamellar extension of the tegular apophysis, 
<emphasis box="[757,805,1761,1784]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="425">Va—</emphasis>
ventro-retrolateral apophysis.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1830,2037]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="426" pageId="2" pageNumber="425">
Palp as in 
<figureCitation box="[315,432,1830,1856]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1688,1712]" captionTargetBox="[154,1420,388,1665]" captionTargetId="figure-125@2.[151,1436,381,1665]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Habitus and male palp of Indozodion lindbergi (Roewer, 1960). A male habitus, dorsal; B female habitus, dorsal; C–F palp, dorsal, retrolateral, prolateral and ventral. Scale bars = 0.2 mm, unless stated otherwise. Abbreviations: Ta—tegular apophysis, Tl—lamellar extension of the tegular apophysis, Va—ventro-retrolateral apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683466" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683466/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="425">Figs 1C–F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[444,514,1830,1856]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1097,1121]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,309,1073]" captionTargetId="figure-82@3.[151,1436,309,1073]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. SEM images of the male palp of Indozodion lindbergi (Roewer, 1960). A retrolateral; B ventral; C distal. Scale bars = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: Co—conductor, Ep—embolus proper, Ev—ventral branch of embolus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683471" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683471/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="425">2A–C</figureCitation>
; femur 3 times longer than wide, 1.25 times shorter than cymbium; patella as long as wide; tibia short, as long as wide, with very long RTA almost 2.5 times longer than tibia itself (
<figureCitation box="[1256,1374,1866,1893]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1688,1712]" captionTargetBox="[154,1420,388,1665]" captionTargetId="figure-125@2.[151,1436,381,1665]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Habitus and male palp of Indozodion lindbergi (Roewer, 1960). A male habitus, dorsal; B female habitus, dorsal; C–F palp, dorsal, retrolateral, prolateral and ventral. Scale bars = 0.2 mm, unless stated otherwise. Abbreviations: Ta—tegular apophysis, Tl—lamellar extension of the tegular apophysis, Va—ventro-retrolateral apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683466" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683466/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="425">Fig. 1C, F</figureCitation>
), and small ventro-retrolateral apophysis (
<emphasis box="[553,581,1903,1928]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="425">Va</emphasis>
) (
<figureCitation box="[605,691,1902,1928]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1688,1712]" captionTargetBox="[154,1420,388,1665]" captionTargetId="figure-125@2.[151,1436,381,1665]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Habitus and male palp of Indozodion lindbergi (Roewer, 1960). A male habitus, dorsal; B female habitus, dorsal; C–F palp, dorsal, retrolateral, prolateral and ventral. Scale bars = 0.2 mm, unless stated otherwise. Abbreviations: Ta—tegular apophysis, Tl—lamellar extension of the tegular apophysis, Va—ventro-retrolateral apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683466" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683466/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="425">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
); tibia and RTA slightly longer than cymbium; RTA almost straight, about 10 times longer than wide (=basal width), tip sharply pointed; cymbium elongate, 2 times longer than wide, lacking folds and tutaculum; bulb oval, 2 times longer than wide; tegular apophysis (
<emphasis box="[1079,1106,1975,2000]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="425">Ta</emphasis>
) long, originating from mesal part of tegulum, almost straight, ca. 4 times longer than wide, with anterior lamellar extension (
<emphasis box="[1208,1231,2010,2036]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="425">Tl</emphasis>
) and hook-like tip (
<figureCitation box="[159,276,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1688,1712]" captionTargetBox="[154,1420,388,1665]" captionTargetId="figure-125@2.[151,1436,381,1665]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Habitus and male palp of Indozodion lindbergi (Roewer, 1960). A male habitus, dorsal; B female habitus, dorsal; C–F palp, dorsal, retrolateral, prolateral and ventral. Scale bars = 0.2 mm, unless stated otherwise. Abbreviations: Ta—tegular apophysis, Tl—lamellar extension of the tegular apophysis, Va—ventro-retrolateral apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683466" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683466/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="426">Figs 1E‒F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[286,322,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1097,1121]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,309,1073]" captionTargetId="figure-82@3.[151,1436,309,1073]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. SEM images of the male palp of Indozodion lindbergi (Roewer, 1960). A retrolateral; B ventral; C distal. Scale bars = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: Co—conductor, Ep—embolus proper, Ev—ventral branch of embolus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683471" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683471/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="426">2B</figureCitation>
); sperm duct not meandering; conductor (
<emphasis box="[785,818,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="426">Co</emphasis>
) small, visible on SEM images only (
<figureCitation box="[1234,1322,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1097,1121]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,309,1073]" captionTargetId="figure-82@3.[151,1436,309,1073]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. SEM images of the male palp of Indozodion lindbergi (Roewer, 1960). A retrolateral; B ventral; C distal. Scale bars = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: Co—conductor, Ep—embolus proper, Ev—ventral branch of embolus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683471" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683471/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="426">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
); embolus broad, originating at about 6 o’clock position and terminating at a 12 o’clock position, bifurcated terminally at about 10:30 o’clock position, ventral branch (
<emphasis box="[602,632,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="426">Ev</emphasis>
) shorter than embolus proper (
<emphasis box="[986,1017,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="426">Ep</emphasis>
), tip sharply pointed, terminating on terminal part of tegular apophysis (
<figureCitation box="[544,667,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1097,1121]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,309,1073]" captionTargetId="figure-82@3.[151,1436,309,1073]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. SEM images of the male palp of Indozodion lindbergi (Roewer, 1960). A retrolateral; B ventral; C distal. Scale bars = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: Co—conductor, Ep—embolus proper, Ev—ventral branch of embolus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683471" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683471/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="426">Fig. 2B‒C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683471" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6683471" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683471/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="426" startId="3.[151,250,1097,1121]" targetBox="[151,1436,309,1073]" targetPageId="3">
